<item>
            <title>[SOLR-12668] Autoscaling Listeners should be executed in the order of their creation</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-12668</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;As found in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-12667&quot; title=&quot;IndexSizeTriggerTest fails often on jenkins&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SOLR-12667&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SOLR-12667&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, autoscaling listeners are not executed in any set order even though it is documented otherwise in the ref guide. It&#8217;s a valid use case to require that listeners are executed in a user-specified order. So a listener B created after listener A for the same event type should always fire after listener A completes.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
